            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Penguin was integrated into Google's core algorithm in 2016 and runs in real-time. It no longer gets separate version numbers or announcements, but it continuously evaluates link quality for every site.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can Penguin penalize you for links you didn't build?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>In theory, negative SEO attacks could trigger Penguin filters. In practice, Google has become much better at ignoring obviously spammy links directed at a site by competitors. The disavow tool exists as insurance for serious cases where spammy links are causing measurable harm.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I build links safely post-Penguin?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Focus on earning links through quality content, digital PR, and genuine relationships. Avoid link exchanges, paid links, and bulk directory submissions. Maintain anchor text diversity with mostly branded and natural anchor text. If a link building tactic feels like a shortcut, Penguin is designed to catch it.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How does Penguin detect manipulative links?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Penguin analyzes link profiles for patterns indicating manipulation: sudden spikes in link acquisition from low-quality sites, unnatural anchor text ratios with 80% or more exact-match keywords, links from irrelevant niches, and patterns consistent with link networks or bulk directory submissions.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I recover from a Penguin hit?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Audit your backlink profile using Ahrefs or Semrush. Identify links from spammy, irrelevant, or paid sources. Attempt removal by contacting webmasters. For links you cannot remove, submit a disavow file through Google Search Console. Since Penguin 4.0 is real-time, rankings can recover within weeks once spammy links are disavowed.</p></div></div>
